**b.)** An unlevered cost of equity is a hypothetical measurement that uses a debt-free model. It can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Cost of Equity}&=\text{Unlevered cost of equity}\\
&+(\text{Unlevered cost of equity} -\text{Cost of debt}) \times (1-\text{Tax rate}) \times \text{Debt-equity ratio}
\end{aligned}$$
